commit.message:
Did a few things:
    * Created default region populations(static members of Region class)
    * Created a Settings class and moved relevant global information
          there. Stuff like soundFX, music, and difficulty.
    * Removed the DataHolder.date member. it's redundant, just access
          the date via DataHolder.sim.date
    * Discovered bug in simulation causing negative population.
          Needs fixing.

Taking new approach to simulation. Will be real time. Commented out scripted events and popup references to the array. App runs without crashing (that's a plus). PlayActivity display stuff (population etc) need to be updated on an interval.
Get Event List in DataHolder and Update Event.java
Update Wiley's Region, Simulator, and Event Classes
Revert Eyes on Map; Eyes Now Hide When Scaled

Affix Eyes to Map; Settings Has Text About There Being No Sound

Eyes are now part of the map image. Setting clearly says sound and music is not in this version.

Settings Screen is Implemented

The buttons toggle correctly, remain toggled when switching an activity, and the difficulty setting is used in the Region  initializer.

BUG: Region array is initialized at startup with the default difficulty. Need to re-initialize when the PlayActivity is created.
Revert Eye Placement, Prepare to Implement Settings Buttons
Map Has Regional Borders, Eyes Placed Better

Region Popup Works -- All global variables go in DataHolder Class!!!!

Popup displays region data.
Variables shared between activities must go in the DataHolder class and are accessed by DataHolder.fieldName.
